RIYDH: Saudi Arabia’s Deputy Defense Minister Khaled bin Salman sauid on Monday he participated in the 18th meeting of the Joint Defense Council of Defense Ministers of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC).
	His participation was based on the directives of Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, the deputy defense minister said in a tweet.
	“During the meeting, we discussed aspects of coordination and integration among the GCC states in the defense field in a way that enhances the security and stability of the region,” he added.